cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.DM 

This paper deals with constraint programming and scheduling problems, which are typically studied in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and programming languages (cs.PL) sub-categories. The use of lazy clause generation solvers and nogood learning also suggests a connection to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The development of efficient propagators for resource constraints involves data structures and algorithms, which are studied in the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the use of benchmark suites and experimental results suggests a connection to the data mining (cs.DM) sub-category.
